-- France Says Four Soldiers Killed in Afghanistan, Five Wounded
-- B y   C a r o l   M a t l a c k
-- 2012-06-09T09:36:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-09/france-says-four-soldiers-killed-in-afghanistan-five-wounded.html
Four French soldiers were killed in
 Afghanistan  and five wounded, including three in a serious
condition, the office of President  Francois Hollande  said today
in a statement.  The soldiers died in the northeast province of  Kapisa  early
today and were attached to an artillery regiment from the French
town of Suippes and a military group based in the city of Lyon,
according to the statement. Hollande said the French defense
minister was leaving immediately for Afghanistan.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Carol Matlack at 
 cmatlack@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
